      <text bytes="652" xml:space="preserve">The '''signal-to-crosstalk ratio''' at a specified point in a [[electrical network|circuit]] is the [[ratio]] of the [[power (physics)|power]] of the wanted [[Signalling (telecommunication)|signal]] to the power of the unwanted signal from another [[Communication channel|channel]]. 

The signals are adjusted in each channel so that they are of equal power at the [[zero transmission level point]] in their respective channels. 

The signal-to-[[crosstalk (electronics)|crosstalk]] ratio is usually expressed in [[decibel|dB]]. 

